3
00:00:07,259 --> 00:00:09,405
Hot storage is online,

4
00:00:09,405 --> 00:00:12,555
for example, on your computer or on your phone.

5
00:00:12,555 --> 00:00:16,320
It's very convenient, but it's not very secure.

6
00:00:16,320 --> 00:00:19,755
On the other hand, cold storage is offline,

7
00:00:19,755 --> 00:00:22,950
not convenient, but it's safe.

8
00:00:22,950 --> 00:00:24,750
The reason is obvious,

9
00:00:24,750 --> 00:00:26,820
if the storage is offline,

10
00:00:26,820 --> 00:00:30,030
then a cyber attacker cannot get to it easily.

11
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:33,600
In general, we can keep a top secret in

12
00:00:33,600 --> 00:00:38,060
a cold storage and put the most frequent used keys.

13
00:00:38,060 --> 00:00:44,000
Here's another way to look at the difference between hot storage and cold storage.

14
00:00:44,000 --> 00:00:50,470
