15
00:00:50,470 --> 00:00:54,470
We can put the most frequently used keys in hot storage.

16
00:00:54,470 --> 00:00:56,345
As we just discussed,

17
00:00:56,345 --> 00:01:02,110
storing your keys of Bitcoins on computers is storing them in a hot storage.

18
00:01:02,110 --> 00:01:05,495
It is online, convenient, but somewhat risky.

19
00:01:05,495 --> 00:01:09,635
On the other hand, you can put your keys of Bitcoins offline.

20
00:01:09,635 --> 00:01:12,485
This is less convenient, but much safer.

21
00:01:12,485 --> 00:01:18,315
You can have the best of both worlds by having both hot storage and cold storage.

22
00:01:18,315 --> 00:01:21,645
For example, you can move coins back and forth,

23
00:01:21,645 --> 00:01:24,860
but then you need to use separate keys and each side

24
00:01:24,860 --> 00:01:28,510
